  "note": "UniswapX PriorityOrder signed as a Permit2 permitWitnessTransferFrom witness — domain=Permit2, verifying_contract=canonical Permit2, primary_type=PermitWitnessTransferFrom, witness_type=PriorityOrder. reactor read from witness order.info.reactor. Base only (PriorityOrderReactor 0x000000001Ec5656…, SDK+BaseScan Exact Match; NOT deployed on mainnet — zero address in SDK map), research §3.2. PriorityOrder KEEPS NESTED input/outputs (PriorityInput/PriorityOutput). MODELING APPROXIMATION: order_kind=\"limit\" — priority orders fix amounts at sign time (the priority fee is the ordering mechanism, not a price-decay curve); IntentOrderKind has no Priority variant so \"limit\" is the least-wrong. The PriorityOutput carries only `amount` (no start/end) → sell_amount=input.amount, buy_min=outputs[0].amount (both read the fixed sign-time amount). cosignerData/cosignature are cosigner-added, EXCLUDED from the swapper witness. selector 0x00000004 is a sign-only placeholder (distinct per family).",
